      "Viral coefficient (K): How many new customers does 1 customer bring? If K=0.2 (1 customer brings 0.2 customers = 20% growth from referrals). K=1.0 means doubling from referrals alone (viral). Viral products (Slack, Dropbox): K=0.5-1.0. Non-viral SaaS: K=0.1-0.3. Increase K by: improve NPS (promoters refer more), add referral incentive (£100 credit), make product shareable (sharing = free marketing).",
      "Product-led growth (PLG): Free trial or freemium model, customer self-serves to value, converts to paid. Example: Figma (free tier, users invite teammates, freemium → paid when needs grow). CAC £500 (much lower than sales model). Conversion: 2-5% free → paid. Works if: product intuitive, network effects (more users = more value), low-touch support.",
